		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Let me rephrase: If I want to bundle an NES ROM with an emulator hardcoded to run this ROM, which emulator for Android is designed for this use case?<br /><br />I'm aware that touch screens aren't very good at representing button presses. But I'm told that dual virtual joysticks are workable: offer two touch areas in each corner, and treat the displacement since contact as a direction. &quot;Tap&quot;, &quot;hold&quot;, and &quot;displace to edge of touch area&quot; are four more inputs on each side. Which NES emulator for Android allows specifying how touch gestures will be translated into NES inputs in each game state? Or should I just learn Android programming and write my own emulator already?

		

